Login to the console with Admin account
Find the IAM Management Console under the Security, Identity, & Compliance section
In left panel under the Access Management console click on "Roles"
Click in "Create Role" button
Choose the "Another AWS account" field
Paste the trusted account ID (number of ARN) into the "Account ID" field
Click on "Next Permissions" button in the boottom of the screen
Choose the type of permissions you want to grant 
Enter the Role name into the "Role Name" field
Click on "Create Role"
Share the link with the trusted account
Make sure that everything works fine
If it is, Congrats! 
